  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does hydraulic car parking work?",
  "response": "Hydraulic car parking systems are designed to maximize parking efficiency by utilizing vertical space. These systems use hydraulic technology to lift and store vehicles in a tiered fashion. Here's how hydraulic car parking typically works:\n\n1. **Entry and Placement**: The driver parks the car at a designated entry point, usually on a platform. This platform is connected to the hydraulic system and serves as the base for lifting and moving the car.\n\n2. **Hydraulic Lift Mechanism**: The hydraulic system comprises pistons, pumps, and fluid reservoirs. When the system is activated, hydraulic pumps push fluid into the pistons, generating the force necessary to lift the platform. The pistons move vertically, elevating the car to an upper level or lowering it to a lower level.\n\n3. **Vertical Storage**: Once the car is lifted, it can be moved into a storage slot. This is done by an automated mechanism that shifts the platform horizontally into an available slot within the vertical structure. Some systems have multiple tiers, allowing several cars to be stacked on top of each other.\n\n4. **Retrieval**: To retrieve the car, the system is activated again to move the platform back to the entry level. The hydraulic lift lowers or raises the platform accordingly, positioning it for easy drive-out access by the driver.\n\n5. **Control System**: Hydraulic car parking systems are typically controlled via a computerized system. The driver may use a keypad, touch screen, or smart card to input commands for parking or retrieving their vehicle. The system keeps track of the available slots and handles the movement and placement of the platforms efficiently.\n\n**Advantages of Hydraulic Car Parking:**\n- **Space Efficiency**: Ideal for urban areas with limited parking space, these systems can significantly increase the parking capacity.\n- **Automation**: Minimal human intervention is required, reducing the chance of parking mishaps.\n- **Flexibility**: Can be installed in various configurations and customized to fit different building structures.\n- **Safety**: Vehicles are securely stored and protected from external damage and theft.\n\n**Disadvantages:**\n- **Initial Cost**: The installation and setup of hydraulic parking systems can be expensive.\n- **Maintenance**: Regular maintenance is required to ensure the hydraulic system and mechanical parts function smoothly.\n- **Limitations**: Not suitable for very large or heavy vehicles due to the weight constraints of the hydraulic lift.\n\nOverall, hydraulic car parking systems provide an innovative solution to parking challenges, particularly in densely populated urban environments.",
